Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Freight conditions across the Midwest tightened again this week.

Spot rates climbed 4.8% week over week while warehouse idle time fell to the lowest level in nine weeks.
Carrier commentary points to faster restocking cycles in industrial tooling, farm equipment, and food packaging.

What to watch next:
- Chicago outbound lanes are recovering first.
- St. Louis remains mixed because broker capacity is still oversupplied.
- Small-warehouse operators are reporting faster inbound turns than national chains.

The signal is not broad enough to call a national recovery, but it is strong enough to justify a closer review of regional demand.
